******
[2] Sindh
Date: Wed 14 Oct 2015
Source: The News [edited]
http://www.thenews.com.pk/Todays-News-4-345519-Dengue,-Congo-fevers-claim-three-more-lives


The number of patients to have died from Congo-Crimean haemorrhagic fever (CCHF) increased to 3, [Kaachi] city health authorities confirmed on Tuesday [13 Oct 2015]. According to the director, 2 patients were said to have died of the CCHF this past week, while a 3rd death was reported earlier in 2015, whereas a 4th was currently battling for his life at an ICU in the CHK.

With respect to CCHF, a 57-year-old woman, resident of DHA, died at the Aga Khan University Hospital (AKUH) on 8 Oct [2015]; however, the city's health authorities were informed of her death on Tuesday [14 Oct 2015].

A male patient, a resident of Orangi Town, was also brought to the AKUH last week with CCHF symptoms, however, he died after the virus had advanced to a stage where his body stopped responding to the medication, Dr Aijaz informed.

A 22-year-old man from Baldia Town was also diagnosed with CCHF and was currently battling for his life at an ICU of the CHK.

[Byline: M. Waqar Bhatti]

